<div class="container-fluid text-center bg-info"
     style="margin-top: 50px;">
    <h1 style="color: blue;">Coupon Network</h1>
    <h2 class="text-primary">PG Technologies, LLC</h2>
    <h3 class="text-primary">Coupon Buddy Program</h3>
    <div class="container-fluid">
        <p style="font-size: 25px; color: black;">
            Traditional print advertising (Newspapers, magazines, mailings, flyers, Brochures, periodicals etc.) are a costly option for the small business and may not be affordable to many businesses. Additionally, Print ads are static and, once printed, cannot be changed until the next printing, thus, leading to higher costs to change and modify the coupon deals. Newspaper & magazine ads can run from $400 to $3,000 depending on the size of an ad and that is generally for one printing, which may have a distribution of 5,000 to 30,000 people. The higher the distribution, the more costly the advertisement. These advertisements, especially the smaller ones, may contain only 1 coupon.
